As a non-wizard, I'm not overly familiar with Manaburn.  But wouldn't a more effective &quot;nerf&quot; be to reduce the damage done on mobs under 33k, proportional to the damage that would be done post 33k?  Say, Manaburn used on mobs between 20 and 32k would be only 70% effective (only 70% of what max damage could be), 10k-19k would be 60% effective, and so on.  It would be more of an incentive for Wizards to hunt the higher end mobs, getting full effectiveness out of MB, but still keeping it useful against mobs under 33k.  With the hardships endured to actually get Manaburn, it seens pretty silly for VI to say &quot;thanks for putting in the hard work, here's a nice slap in the face for you.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ughostofgreem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghost of Greem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/30/02 11:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MANABURN - NERFED ON TEST!</span><hr size=1> WAHHHHHHHHHH WAAAAAAAHHHAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA IM MELTING ME MANABURN AHHH I CANT KILL THE THE OVERLOARD OF EVERQUEST WITH MY MAGICAL ABILITIES WAAHHHA WAHHH EVERYBODY GET AND START A RIOT IN VERANT COURTYARD <p><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Greem/fullsize/MITHCSMAN2.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 5376<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/30/02 11:11 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg