<br>
This is a rediculous statement. VI-SOE should have seen this coming <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> way</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> before they even released Luclin. They gave us a very powerful tool, and it was only time until enough wizards got it that it would be used to kill mobs that normally required large amounts of players.<br>
<br>
This move is just more proof that the designers on the EQ Dev team aren't looking past selling the product. They dangle the carrot, just long enough to see an increase in a certain area, and then nerf the hell out of it in the name of balance. It's complete bull shit.<br>
<br>
Imagine leasing a car that got 80 miles to the gallon, and then all of a sudden, the government made a law that said &quot;since we like oil so much, you cannot get more than 40 miles to the gallon.&quot;. People would freak out.<br>
<br>
VI has a track record of giving us stuff that's way to powerful, and then nerfing it. Except one thing that they'd never nerf, because they built the entire game around it -- Complete Heal.<br>
Imagine if all of a sudden, they decided to change CHeal to only heal 5000 hitpoints, and it was over time (like the HoT spells clerics currently have). For most warriors, that is a complete heal, but it would totally mess up every encounter from level 50 up. There'd be no more Chain CHealing. There goes just about every 33k+ hitpoint mob in the game.<br>
<br>
What would have made more sense, and would have probably been easier on the game community, would have been upgrading those key mobs that made them choose to nerf MB in the first place: Phinny, Venril Sathir, the VP dragons, and so on. Make them in line with the rest of the game.<br>
<br>
Just last night I was reading through the Class Balance topic. There is a thread there titled '<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Can game balance happen without a change to the old world</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?' You know what? It can't. <br>
They've given us 4 different games with 4 different rulesets, and they're letting us play our characters anywhere we want. This means that some areas are going to be way underpowered for players that have adventured in the newer (and harder) areas.<br>
They upgraded the planes from being 32k bosses. Why the hell didn't they upgrade the rest of the places, over time?<br>
<br>
It's swift moves like this that cause people to say EQ teams has no fucking clue what they're doing, and moves like this reinforce it. <p><center>
